13/12/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The Romanian troops serving in Kandahar, Afganistan, will be relocated to a new military base starting later this month. 
The defence ministry issued a statement Sunday (12 December) saying that the troops will be deployed at a base built by coalition allies earlier this year. 
Romania has contributed 504 troops to the international effort in Afghanistan.
In other news, a Europol liaison office with Romania opened in The Hague on Friday. 
It is expected to boost co-operation between Europol and Romania, a candidate for EU membership, as well as strengthen the fight against organised crime. 
(Rompres - 13/12/04; Romania Actualitati - 10/12/04)
